    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"excerpt":"Hi Friends 👋, Welcome To aGuideHub!  To show mui alert as toast in react js, you can use this code . This will show mui alert as toast in React JS. Today, I am…","html":"<p>Hi Friends 👋,</p>\n<p>Welcome To aGuideHub! </p>\n<p>To show mui alert as toast in react js, you can use this code <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;Snackbar open={open} autoHideDuration={3000} onClose={handleClose}></code>. This will show mui alert as toast in React JS.</p>\n<p>Today, I am going to show you, how to show mui alert as toast in react js.</p>\n<h2>Installation</h2>\n<p>Install the following packages to use mui Alert in react js.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">npm</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">npm install @mui<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>material @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>react @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>styled</code></pre></div>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">yarn</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">yarn add @mui<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>material @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>react @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>styled</code></pre></div>\n<p>Table of contents</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Install MUI and create a new React app.</li>\n<li>Import Material-UI alert.</li>\n<li>Use the Alert Component</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Step 1: Install MUI and create a new React app.</h3>\n<p>First you have to install the React project. You should use <code class=\"language-text\">create-react-app</code> command to create a new React project.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">npx create<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>react<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\ncd my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\nnpm start</code></pre></div>\n<h3>Step 2: Import Material-UI alert.</h3>\n<p>After installing <code class=\"language-text\">MUI</code>, you have to import your React component. To do this, add the following line to the top of your component file.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"react\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> Snackbar<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> Alert <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"@mui/material\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<h3>Step 3: Use the Alert Component</h3>\n<p>You can use the <code class=\"language-text\">Alert</code> component in your react js. For example, The Alert component is used to display important messages or notifications to users. You can use <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;Alert></code> component make a alert box in react js.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Alert onClose<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>handleClose<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> severity<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"success\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    This is a success message<span class=\"token operator\">!</span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>Alert<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<h2>MUI material show mui alert as toast example.</h2>\n<p>The below code is an example, to do custom of mui alert, you need to import <code class=\"language-text\">Alert</code> Component. When the <code class=\"language-text\">Show Toast</code> button is clicked, the toast will display for 3 seconds <code class=\"language-text\">(3000 milliseconds)</code> and then automatically turn off.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">App.js</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"react\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> Snackbar<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> Alert <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"@mui/material\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">App</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>open<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> setOpen<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> React<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">useState</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token boolean\">false</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">handleOpen</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token function\">setOpen</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token boolean\">true</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">handleClose</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">event<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> reason</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">if</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>reason <span class=\"token operator\">===</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"clickaway\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token function\">setOpen</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token boolean\">false</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>button onClick<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>handleOpen<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> type<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"button\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        Show Toast\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>button<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Snackbar open<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>open<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> autoHideDuration<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token number\">3000</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> onClose<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>handleClose<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Alert onClose<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>handleClose<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> severity<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"success\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n          This is a success message<span class=\"token operator\">!</span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>Alert<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>Snackbar<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> App<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>In the above code example, I have used the <code class=\"language-text\">@mui/material</code> component and show mui alert as toast in react js.</p>\n<p>Check the output of the above code example.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/784b819b23e251c055dd21766fb8803a/7545b/alert-as-toast.webp\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 93.0379746835443%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/webp;base64,UklGRk4AAABXRUJQVlA4IEIAAABwAwCdASoUABMAPslSnkunpKKhsAwA8BkJZwDOdCHe1AUQowAA/uev9bcfQxA9Yg7+T6D9YOia9xv+H/0mZEAAAAA='); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"React, Mui, change-icon\"\n        title=\"React, Mui, change-icon\"\n        src=\"/static/784b819b23e251c055dd21766fb8803a/8aab1/alert-as-toast.webp\"\n        srcset=\"/static/784b819b23e251c055dd21766fb8803a/81b7c/alert-as-toast.webp 158w,\n/static/784b819b23e251c055dd21766fb8803a/6ea66/alert-as-toast.webp 315w,\n/static/784b819b23e251c055dd21766fb8803a/8aab1/alert-as-toast.webp 630w,\n/static/784b819b23e251c055dd21766fb8803a/7545b/alert-as-toast.webp 741w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Here, we are provided code sandbox links for the above program show mui alert as toast in react js. Then you can use whenever you want and do the changes as per your requirements.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://aguidehub.com/codesandbox/?code=dazzling-satoshi-3tf3sy\" rel=\"nofollow\"  target=\"_BLANK\" >Try it Yourself</a></p>\n<p>All the best 👍</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"How to show mui alert as toast in react js?","tags":["React"],"date":"June 26, 2023","description":"Example of show mui alert as toast in React js with step by step tutorial - aGuideHub","social_image":"media/template/reactjs.jpg"}},"prev":{"frontmatter":{"title":"How to show mui alert without icon in react js?"},"fields":{"slug":"/blog/2023-06-27-how-to-show-mui-alert-without-icon-in-react-js/"}},"next":{"frontmatter":{"title":"How to change text color of mui alert in react js?"},"fields":{"slug":"/blog/2023-06-26-how-to-change-text-color-of-mui-alert-in-react-js/"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/blog/2023-06-26-how-to-show-mui-alert-as-toast-in-react-js/","prevSlug":"/blog/2023-06-27-how-to-show-mui-alert-without-icon-in-react-js/","nextSlug":"/blog/2023-06-26-how-to-change-text-color-of-mui-alert-in-react-js/"}},
